    <title>Help Low-Income Students Access the Promise of AP</title>
    <link>https://www.collegeboard.org/membership/all-access/academic/help-low-income-students-access-promise-ap</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; rel=&quot;&quot; resource=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/AP%20video.png?itok=QXG1Pw9x&quot;&gt;&lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/AP%20video.png?itok=QXG1Pw9x&quot; alt=&quot;Help Low-Income Students Access the Promise of AP&quot; title=&quot;Help Low-Income Students Access the Promise of AP&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-author field-type-text field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Andrew Elwell, Director, Communications&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-newsletter-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/taxonomy/term/391&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;advanced placement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/taxonomy/term/566&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/every-student-succeeds-act&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Every Student Succeeds Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/essa&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;ESSA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/ap-exams&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;AP Exams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since 1998, the federal government has provided states with dedicated funding to offset the cost of AP Exams for low-income students under a Title I program called the Advanced Placement Test Fee Program. When the Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA) goes into effect, that dedicated funding will be eliminated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below, hear from AP students and Trevor Packer, Senior Vice President of AP &amp;amp; Instruction, on why this funding is important and what you can do to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To learn more, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://professionals.collegeboard.org/testing/states-local-governments/new-education-policies/essa-federal-funding-ap?excmpid=VT-00211&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;collegeboard.org/ap-essa&lt;/a&gt;. If you are interested in advocating on behalf of low-income AP students, please email &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:apfunding@collegeboard.org&quot;&gt;apfunding@collegeboard.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
